Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}. Stir-fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook
> lardons thoroughly.

Once the bacon is golden, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until
browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess
fat. Season with @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The
> mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in half the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the @sugar{1%tsp}
and @water{200%ml} for the sauce, @tomato passata{1%400g jar},
@Italian style herbs{1%tsp} and @red wine jus paste{22%g}.

Stir together well, then bring the Bolognese to the boil and simmer until
thickened, ~{15-20%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it gets too thick.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}
for the pasta.

Cut the @medium tomatoes{2}(cut into 1cm chunks). Put the
@balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing into a
#medium bowl{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the tomato to the dressing, stir to combine, then set aside.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and place on a #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the garlic bread,
remaining garlic and half the @Parmigiano Reggiano{40%g}. Spread the cheesy
mixture on top of the ciabatta, then set aside.

Add the @spaghetti{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, bake the ciabatta on the top shelf of your oven until
the cheese is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the Bolognese has thickened, taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} if needed.

When ready, add the cooked spaghetti to the Bolognese and toss to coat. Add a
splash of water if it's a little thick.

When everything's ready, add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the bowl of tomatoes and
toss together in the dressing.

Cut the cheesy garlic bread into triangles.

Serve up your ultimate beef and bacon spaghetti bolognese in #bowls{} with the
salad and garlic bread as sides.

Sprinkle the remaining parmesan over the pasta to finish.

Enjoy!